│                                                                                            │
│ ### 5. Conclusion                                                                          │
│                                                                                            │
│ The root cause of the assertion failure was a discrepancy between the VPlan and legacy     │
│ cost models, caused by the legacy model's failure to correctly identify a "narrowed        │
│ reduction". By improving the detection logic in `getArithmeticReductionCost`, the legacy   │
│ model's cost estimation becomes more accurate and aligns with the VPlan model's decision.  │
│ This prevents the assertion from firing and allows the vectorizer to correctly decide      │
│ against vectorizing this specific loop, which is the more profitable choice.               │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                                            │
